description.narrative: This award strives to help nations effectively establish the conditions and capacity for achieving peace, security, and stability. More specifically, this includes INTERNATIONAL POLICE PEACEKEEPING OPERATIONS SUPPORT[Covers miscellaneous contractual services not otherwise classified under Miscellaneous/Other Contractual Services.]. INTERNATIONAL POLICE PEACEKEEPING OPERATIONS SUPPORT. CIVILIAN POLICE PROGRAM. INTERNATIONAL POLICE PEACEKEEPING OPERATIONS SUPPORT [Covers miscellaneous contractual services not otherwise classified under Miscellaneous/Other Contractual Services.]. Management and professional support services generally aim at improving the efficiency or effectiveness of management or administrative systems and normally take the form of information, opinion, advice, training or direct assistance. Contracts may be with firms or individuals.. Covers miscellaneous contractual services not otherwise classified. [Covers miscellaneous contractual services not otherwise classified under Miscellaneous/Other Contractual Services.]. Covers miscellaneous contractual services such as A&E contracts and IT site preparation by the PBA, GSA, and commercial contracts, among other things.. Covers miscellaneous contractual services not otherwise classified. [Covers miscellaneous contractual services such as A&E contracts and IT site preparation by the PBA, GSA, and commercial contracts, among other things.]. Covers miscellaneous contractual services not otherwise classified under Miscellaneous/Other Contractual Services.. IPPOS police peacekeeping implementation contract. [Covers miscellaneous contractual services not otherwise classified.]. INTERNATIONAL POLICE PEACEKEEPING OPERATIONS SUPPORT[Covers miscellaneous contractual services such as A&E contracts and IT site preparation by the PBA, GSA, and commercial contracts, among other things.]. Information has been redacted in accordance with the two principled exceptions defined in the Foreign Aid Transparency and Accountability Act (FATAA) of 2016: the health and security of implementing partners, and the national interest of the United States..

Through educational programs and technical support, help foreign partners professionalize their military forces, ensuring that their force can develop and maintain the requisite capacity to effectively carry out its military mission through reliance on discipline, accountability, effective professional standards, and technical expertise. In addition, activities assist foreign partners so that their military forces reliably demonstrate consistent support for adherence to norms of human rights; support the concept of civilian executive authority/control of the military; and have the capacity for institutional and security sector reform.

To help nations effectively establish the conditions and capacity for achieving peace, security, and stability; and for responding effectively against arising threats to national or international security and stability.
